headline: Does Autodesk’s Latest Earnings Guidance Signal a Fair Price in 2025?
summary: If you are debating whether to buy, hold, or sell Autodesk stock, you are not alone. The narrative around this software innovator always seems to spark strong opinions from investors on both sides. Autodesk has seen its share price slide slightly recently, with a 4.8% drop in the past week and a 3.5% dip over the past month. If you step back, you will notice the longer trend is still up, with a 5.0% gain year to date and a solid 7.9% rise over the last twelve months. Looking even further...

headline: 1 Large-Cap Stock with Impressive Fundamentals and 2 We Ignore
summary: Large-cap stocks usually command their industries because they have the scale to drive market trends. The flip side though is that their sheer size can limit growth as expanding further becomes an increasingly challenging task.
